Paederus riparius ( Linnaeus, 1758 )
is found throughout Europe, in Egypt and Algeria and Turkey , Iran , and central Asia (
; Smetana 2004). It was first collected from Anzali (
) and an unknown locality along the Caspian Sea shores (Majidi-Shad et al. 1989). Smetana (2004) reported this species from Iran without mentioning the locality. It has been recently collected from Gorgan at the eastern side of the Caspian Sea (Samin et al. 2011a) and Shaurud in Semnan Province (Samin et al. 2011b). We collected
P. riparius
from Macu in north-western Iran alongside the Turkey-Azerbaijan borders ( Table 1 ). This species was assumed to be a western Palaearctic species (
), but Piryugin (2010) believes it is more a Holarctic species.
